Measurements (in mm). Body length: 4.43-5.57 (mean 4.90). Body width (metathorax or abdominal segments 
I-II
) up to 1.37. Head width: 0.70-0.84 (mean 0.71).

This species lives on various species of Campanula ( C. glomerata L., C. incurva Auch., C. latifolia L., C. persicifolia L., C. rapunculus L., C. rhomboidalis L., C. thyrsoides L., C. trachelium L.) in central Europe ( Hoffmann 1958 ;
Smreczynski 1976
; Caldara and Legalov 2016 ). It was never reported to feed on C. cervicaria L., a species widely distributed in Europe. Larvae are seed feeders developing inside seed capsules.
